{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The transparent nature of blockchain transactions means that vulnerabilities in smart contracts could be exploited by anyone with access to the blockchain, magnifying security risks (Jin et al. 2019).",
    "Mitigating these data security challenges demands the implementation of appropriate measures to secure blockchain networks and smart contracts.",
    "Multi-factor authentication and encryption can bolster access protection, permitting only authorised parties to engage in transactions (Şahan et al. 2019).",
    "Additionally, conducting audits and tests on smart contracts can unearth and address vulnerabilities, thereby reducing the risk of attacks and data breaches (Jin et al. 2019).",
    "Finally, it is essential to consider the legal implications of deploying blockchain technology within the framework of data security laws."
  ],
